---
/**
 * Subtle disclosure for the homepage Einstein hat wireframe background.
 * Rendered only when BaseLayout has einsteinBg enabled.
 */
---

<details class="einstein-bg-info fixed bottom-5 left-5 z-50 max-w-[min(18rem,calc(100vw-2.5rem))]">
  <summary class="einstein-bg-info-summary">
    Shape-shifting hats
  </summary>
  <div class="einstein-bg-info-panel mt-2 space-y-2 divider-rule-t">
    <p>
      The backdrop is a wireframe view of the <strong>H7/H8 hat continuum</strong>—a family of
      aperiodic monotiles (the “Einstein hat” story) that morph between two shapes while still
      tiling the plane. The implementation follows Craig Kaplan’s continuum demo.
    </p>
    <p class="flex flex-wrap gap-x-3 gap-y-1">
      <a
        href="https://cs.uwaterloo.ca/~csk/hat/h7h8.html"
        class="underline decoration-from-font underline-offset-2 hover:opacity-80"
        >Kaplan’s H7/H8 explorer</a
      >
      <a
        href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2303.10798"
        class="underline decoration-from-font underline-offset-2 hover:opacity-80"
        >Smith et al. (2023)</a
      >
      <a
        href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Einstein_problem"
        class="underline decoration-from-font underline-offset-2 hover:opacity-80"
        >Einstein problem (Wikipedia)</a
      >
    </p>
  </div>
</details>

<style>
  .einstein-bg-info-summary {
    list-style: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    opacity: 0.55;
    transition: opacity 0.2s ease;
  }

  .einstein-bg-info-summary:hover,
  details.einstein-bg-info:focus-within > .einstein-bg-info-summary,
  details.einstein-bg-info[open] > .einstein-bg-info-summary {
    opacity: 1;
  }

  .einstein-bg-info-summary::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }

  .einstein-bg-info-panel {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    border-radius: 0.375rem;
    padding: 0.5rem 0.625rem;
    margin-left: -0.125rem;
    margin-right: -0.125rem;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-bg) 82%, transparent);
    backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
  }

  .einstein-bg-info-panel strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .einstein-bg-info-panel a {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }
</style>
